# Site-wide cross-origin isolation.
#
# Required by StackBlitz's WebContainer (Node-in-browser uses SharedArrayBuffer,
# which only works in cross-origin-isolated documents). Applied site-wide
# because agent clusters are inherited from the top-level browsing context —
# an iframe can only be isolated if the embedding page is isolated too.
#
# The trade-off lives on cross-origin iframes elsewhere on the site (YouTube,
# Tailwind play, TS playground, etc.): they need either to send COEP
# themselves OR be tagged with the `credentialless` iframe attribute. See
# SandboxCallout.astro and VideoCallout.astro for that tag.
#
# This file is read by Netlify and Cloudflare Pages out of the build output
# root. Vercel equivalent (vercel.json):
#   {
#     "headers": [{
#       "source": "/(.*)",
#       "headers": [
#         { "key": "Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy",   "value": "same-origin" },
#         { "key": "Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy", "value": "credentialless" }
#       ]
#     }]
#   }
# Nginx equivalent (inside the relevant location block):
#   add_header Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy   "same-origin"     always;
#   add_header Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy "credentialless"  always;

/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
